      • isNameUnique

        public boolean isNameUnique()
        Description copied from class: SailPointObject
        Return true if the object name can be used as a unique database key. It is almost always true, but a few classes like SODConstraint want to allow names for lookup, but cannot guarantee that the names are unique.

        This is relevant only if hasName is true.

      • isAdditionalEntitlements

        public boolean isAdditionalEntitlements()
        Return true if the identity has any additional entitlements and this is an assigned role. Note that this is not the traditional definition of "additional entitlements" (meaning any entitlement that is not part of a role detection), but any entitlements that a user has that are not part of a permitted or required role definition.
